The paper is primarily focused on the training of neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the role of depth in improving the conditioning of kernel matrices, which is related to optimization and numerical analysis, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which are both relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper provides a generalization of previous results, which involves information theory (cs.IT), making it a possible sub-category as well.
